@startuml
' Professional styling - pure white background
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam actor {
  BackgroundColor #FFFFFF
  BorderColor #2C3E50
  FontColor #2C3E50
  FontStyle bold
}
skinparam participant {
  BackgroundColor #FFFFFF
  BorderColor #2C3E50
  BorderThickness 1.5
  FontColor #2C3E50
  FontSize 12
}
skinparam arrow {
  Color #5D6D7E
  Thickness 1.5
}
skinparam sequenceMessage {
  FontColor #2C3E50
  FontSize 11
}

actor "User" as User

participant "Web Interface" as Web
participant "Simulation Core" as Core
participant "Algorithm Repository" as AlgoRepo
participant "Visualization" as Viz

User -> Web : 1. Opens setup page
Web --> User : Displays configuration form

User -> Web : 2. Configures simulation\n(duration, sensors, targets)
User -> Web : 3. Selects algorithms\n(SPSA, Accelerated SPSA)
User -> Web : 4. Clicks "Run Simulation"

Web -> Core : 5. Start simulation with\nselected parameters
Core -> Core : 6. Generate targets movement\n(add noise if enabled)

loop For each time step
    Core -> AlgoRepo : 7. Execute selected algorithms
    AlgoRepo --> Core : Return estimates
    Core -> Core : 8. Store results
end

Core --> Web : 9. Simulation complete\n(estimates & errors)

Web -> Viz : 10. Generate plots
Viz --> Web : Trajectories & convergence plots

Web --> User : 11. Display results:\n- Trajectory plots\n- Error convergence\n- Algorithm comparison

@enduml
